---


Author Name: **Mike Denio**
Original Redmine Issue: 457 from https://www.veripool.org
Original Date: 2012-03-15


---

I'm creating a derrived clock through a very simple clock gate, but the derrived clock is being treated like a delayed signal such that any changes are not acted upon until a subsequent call to _eval(). The following test code will drive the test pin "results" to 0, while on other simulators, it will be driven to 1.

I don't think it's anything I'm doing wrong. Please let me know otherwise, but it seems that the resulting model code generated in the function Vtb::_eval() would preclude this from ever working properly.

Here is the Verlog. If it's poorly coded, please keep in mind I'm a software guy :) .

-----------
```
`timescale 1 ps / 1 ps

module tb ( gclk, rst_n );
input   gclk;
input   rst_n;

wire    gclk;
wire    rst_n;
wire    clk_gated;
wire    test_sig;
wire    results;

clockgate       clockgate( .in_clk(gclk), .en(1'b1), .out_clk(clk_gated) );
test_master     test_master( .gclk(gclk), .test_sig(test_sig) );
test_slave      test_slave_fail( .dclk(clk_gated), .test_sig(test_sig), .results(results) );
endmodule

//
// failing clockgate module
//
module clockgate (in_clk, en, out_clk);
input   in_clk;            
input   en;            
output  out_clk;        

wire    in_clk;
wire    en;
wire    out_clk;
reg     en_reg;

assign  out_clk  = (in_clk & en_reg);

always @ (posedge in_clk)
begin
     if( en_reg != en )
         en_reg <= #1 en;
end 
endmodule


//
// test_master
//
module test_master (gclk, test_sig);
input   gclk;            
output  test_sig;       

wire    gclk;
reg     test_sig;

initial 
begin
  test_sig = 1'd0;
end

always @ (gclk)
begin
     if( gclk )
         test_sig <= #1 1'b0;
     else        
         test_sig <= #1 1'b1;
end
endmodule


//
// test_slave
//
module test_slave (dclk, test_sig, results);
input   dclk;            
input   test_sig;       
output  results;       

wire    dclk;
wire    test_sig;
reg     results;

initial 
begin
  results  = 1'd0;
end

always @ (posedge dclk)
begin
     if( test_sig )
         results <= #1 1'b1;
     else
         results <= #1 1'b0;
end
endmodule


```
